{{Use British English|date=October 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox company | name = Tesla Grohmann Automation GmbH | logo = Tesla Grohmann Automation Logo.png | former_name = Grohmann Engineering GmbH (1963–2017) | type = [[Subsidiary]] | industry = Engineering | founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1963}} | founder = Klaus Grohmann | hq_location_city = [[Prüm]] | hq_location_country = Germany | key_people = {{Plainlist| * Lothar Thommes<ref name="imprint">{{cite web |url=https://teslagrohmannautomation.de/de/imprint |title=Impressum |website=Tesla Grohmann Automation |language=de}}</ref> * Michael Meens<ref name="imprint" /> * Stephan Werkman<ref name="imprint" /> * Susan Repo<ref name="imprint" /> * Marc Cerda<ref name="imprint" /> }} | num_employees = 800 | num_employees_year = 2017 | parent = [[Tesla, Inc.]] (2017–present) | website = {{URL|https://teslagrohmannautomation.de/en|teslagrohmannautomation.de}} }}
'''Tesla Grohmann Automation GmbH''' (formerly '''Grohmann Engineering GmbH''') is a German engineering company based in [[Prüm]]. The company operates a development center in [[Neutraubling]], as well as support offices in [[Chandler, Arizona]], and [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://teslagrohmannautomation.de/en/contact |title=Contact |website=Tesla Grohmann Automation}}</ref> The company was founded in 1963 by Klaus Grohman and acquired by [[Tesla, Inc.]] in January 2017.
Although the company makes cars, it is primarily a technology company. The product portfolio includes machinery for the production of [[microprocessor]]s and memory chips, [[airbag]] sensors and [[power steering]] controllers, as well as systems for the production of door and roof seals, lithium-ion [[battery cell]]s and modules. Among other things, the company manufactures robotics that are used in the battery and electronics production for [[Tesla, Inc.]] at its [[Gigafactory 1]].<ref>[http://www.intel.com/pressroom/archive/releases/2010/20100303corp_a.htm Intel Honors 16 Companies with Preferred Quality Supplier Award], March 2010</ref>
The firm works closely with universities within dual track studies of [[Mechanical Engineering]] and [[Robotic Process Automation]].<ref>[https://www.teslagrohmannautomation.de/en/apprenticeship Dual-track University-level studies at Tesla Grohmann Automation], March 2018</ref> In addition, it provides training in the field of Technical Product Design, Industrial Mechanics, CNC Operation, Construction Technology, IT, Mechatronics and Industrial Electronic Technology.<ref>[https://www.teslagrohmannautomation.de/en/apprenticeship Tesla Grohmann Automation Apprenticeship], March 2018</ref>
== History == Grohmann Engineering was founded by Klaus Grohmann in 1963.<ref name="ft">{{cite web |url=https://www.ft.com/content/065b2cec-a5b1-11e6-8b69-02899e8bd9d1 |title=Tesla buys German engineer for European expansion |first1=Patrick |last1=McGee |first2=Peter |last2=Campbell |date=8 November 2017 |website=[[Financial Times]]}}</ref> In November 2016, the company's stakeholders (including the {{ill|Deutsche Beteiligungs AG|de}}, which owned 25%) agreed to sell the company to American automotive company [[Tesla Motors]].<ref name="ft" /> The company had 700 employees at the time.<ref name="ft" /> The deal was completed on 3 January 2017, at which point the company employed 800 people.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.welt.de/regionales/rheinland-pfalz-saarland/article161281524/Uebernahme-von-Grohmann-durch-Tesla-abgeschlossen.html |title=Übernahme von Grohmann durch Tesla abgeschlossen |date=18 January 2017 |website=[[Welt (German TV channel)|Welt]]}}</ref>
In April 2017, founder Klaus Grohmann left the company due to a dispute with Tesla CEO [[Elon Musk]]. Musk demanded the company halt production for competitors, such as [[BMW]] and [[Daimler AG]], to focus on the Model 3.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-tesla-germany-exclusive-idUSKBN17T2IY Tesla's Klaus Grohmann ousted after clash with CEO Musk] Reuters, April 2017</ref>
By discontinuing business relations with all customers except Tesla, the company's union was concerned with wage levels and with jobs in the long term if electric cars did not have the expected success.<ref>[https://www.golem.de/news/deutschland-tesla-mitarbeiter-drohen-mit-streik-1704-127338.html Tesla-Mitarbeiter drohen mit Streik], Golem, April 2017</ref> Tesla then offered Grohmann employees 150 euros a month and employee stock options worth $10,000 with a payout over the following four years, as well as a cash payment of 1000 euros. Tesla did not comment on the required collective agreement.<ref>[http://www.wiwo.de/unternehmen/auto/tarifstreit-mit-tesla-ig-metall-setzt-bei-grohmann-auf-kompromiss-/19723484.html Tarifstreit mit Tesla: IG Metall setzt bei Grohmann auf Kompromiss], April 2017</ref> In October 2017, the company agreed with union representatives on a competitive pay structure. According to the chairman of the works council, the future remuneration was at the level of the collective agreement valid for the industry.<ref>[https://www.welt.de/wirtschaft/article169760888/Tesla-gibt-deutschen-Mitarbeitern-deutliche-Gehaltserhoehung.html Deutschland: Tesla einigt sich auf deutliche Gehaltssteigerung], September 2017</ref>
